            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black text-gray-800 tracking-tight">Architectures of Intelligence</h1>
            <p class="mt-4 text-lg md:text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">An interactive deep-dive into the world
                of Large Language Models, from their creation to their impact on our future.</p>
        </header>

        <section id="introduction" class="mb-20">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                <div class="kpi-card lg:col-span-2">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">What is a Large Language Model (LLM)?</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">An LLM is a type of AI built on a neural network, trained on vast
                        quantities of text and code. Its core function is to understand patterns and predict the next
                        most likely piece of a sequence‚Äîa "token." While simple in concept, at massive scale this
                        enables complex emergent abilities like reasoning, summarization, and creativity.</p>
                    <p class="text-gray-600">Think of it like an apprentice who has read an entire library. It doesn't
                        memorize every book but learns the underlying structure of language, style, and knowledge to
                        generate new, coherent text.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="kpi-card text-center flex flex-col justify-center items-center bg-[#0D6EFD] text-white">
                    <span class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-black">15T+</span>
                    <span class="mt-2 text-lg font-semibold">Tokens Trained</span>
                    <p class="text-sm mt-1 opacity-80">(e.g., Llama 3)</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="creation" class="mb-20">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-12">The Making of a Mind: The LLM Lifecycle</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">

                <div class="kpi-card">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-6">From Rules to Attention: A Brief History</h3>
                    <div class="relative">
                        <div class="timeline-item">
                            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                            <p class="font-semibold text-lg">1950s-1970s: Rule-Based NLP</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Systems like ELIZA used handcrafted rules, which were
                                brittle and couldn't handle ambiguity.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="timeline-item">
                            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                            <p class="font-semibold text-lg">1980s-2000s: Statistical Revolution</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">A shift to learning statistical patterns from data, using
                                techniques like N-grams.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="timeline-item">
                            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                            <p class="font-semibold text-lg">Early 2010s: Recurrent Networks (LSTMs)</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Deep learning with LSTMs captured long-range dependencies
                                but processed text sequentially, creating a bottleneck.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="timeline-item border-l-transparent">
                            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                            <p class="font-semibold text-lg">2017: The Transformer</p>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">The "Attention Is All You Need" paper introduced a parallel
                                processing architecture, enabling massive scaling and giving birth to modern LLMs.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="kpi-card">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-6">The Data & Training Pipeline</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-6">Foundational models are not programmed, they are trained. This
                        involves a multi-stage process to source, clean, and feed massive datasets into the model, which
                        is then refined for safety and helpfulness.</p>
                    <div>
                        <div class="flowchart-node">1. Data Sourcing
                            <br><span class="text-xs font-normal text-gray-600">(Common Crawl, Books, Code)</span></div>
                        <div class="flowchart-arrow">‚Üì</div>
                        <div class="flowchart-node">2. Pre-processing
                            <br><span class="text-xs font-normal text-gray-600">(Filtering, Deduplication)</span></div>
                        <div class="flowchart-arrow">‚Üì</div>
                        <div class="flowchart-node">3. Pre-training
                            <br><span class="text-xs font-normal text-gray-600">(Self-supervised learning on GPUs)</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flowchart-arrow">‚Üì</div>
                        <div class="flowchart-node">4. Alignment
                            <br><span class="text-xs font-normal text-gray-600">(Fine-tuning & RLHF)</span></div>
                        <div class="flowchart-arrow">‚Üì</div>
                        <div class="flowchart-node bg-green-200 border-green-500">‚úÖ Deployed & Helpful LLM</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="landscape" class="mb-20">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-12">The Competitive Landscape</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-5 gap-8 items-center">

                <div class="kpi-card md:col-span-3">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Frontier Model Comparison</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-4">Leading models compete on a range of capabilities. While some,
                        like GPT-4o, excel at general reasoning, others like Gemini lead in multimodality, Claude in
                        safety, and Llama in open-source customizability.</p>
                    <div class="chart-container h-80 md:h-96">
                        <canvas id="modelComparisonChart"></canvas>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="kpi-card md:col-span-2">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Ecosystem Strategy: Open vs. Closed</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-4">The market is split. Proprietary APIs offer ease of use and
                        cutting-edge performance, while open-source models provide control, privacy, and customization.
                    </p>
                    <div class="chart-container h-80 md:h-96">
                        <canvas id="ecosystemSplitChart"></canvas>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="capabilities" class="mb-20">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-12">Capabilities Unleashed: Real-World Impact</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                <div class="kpi-card">
                    <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                        <span class="text-3xl mr-4">‚öïÔ∏è</span>
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">Healthcare</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">LLMs are automating clinical notes, assisting in diagnostics by
                        analyzing symptoms and medical images, and powering virtual training simulators for medical
                        students.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="kpi-card">
                    <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                        <span class="text-3xl mr-4">üè¶</span>
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">Finance</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Applications include real-time fraud detection, 24/7 customer
                        support chatbots, and automating the analysis of dense financial reports like 10-K filings.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="kpi-card">
                    <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
                        <span class="text-3xl mr-4">üéì</span>
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">Education</h3>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">LLMs act as personalized tutors, help teachers generate lesson
                        plans and quizzes, and power adaptive learning platforms like Duolingo.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="challenges" class="mb-20">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-12">Inherent Limitations & Ethical Challenges</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
                <div class="kpi-card">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Security Risks: A New Attack Surface</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-4">The OWASP Top 10 for LLMs highlights new vulnerabilities.
                        Prompt Injection, where attackers hijack the model's instructions, is the most prominent threat.
                    </p>
                    <div class="chart-container h-80 md:h-96">
                        <canvas id="securityRisksChart"></canvas>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="kpi-card">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Bias, Hallucinations & Environmental Cost</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-4">Models reflect biases from their training data, can
                        confidently "hallucinate" incorrect facts, and have a significant environmental footprint.</p>
                    <div class="space-y-6">
                        <div class="flex items-center">
                            <span class="text-2xl mr-4">üåç</span>
                            <div>
                                <p class="font-semibold">Environmental Footprint</p>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Training a single large model can consume
                                    <strong>700,000L of water</strong> and have a carbon footprint of multiple cars.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex items-center">
                            <span class="text-2xl mr-4">üí¨</span>
                            <div>
                                <p class="font-semibold">Hallucinations</p>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">A core failure mode where models generate plausible but
                                    false information due to their probabilistic nature.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex items-center">
                            <span class="text-2xl mr-4">‚öñÔ∏è</span>
                            <div>
                                <p class="font-semibold">Amplified Bias</p>
                                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">LLMs can perpetuate and amplify societal biases related
                                    to gender, race, and profession found in training data.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="future" class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-12">The Next Horizon</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <div class="kpi-card">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">The Rise of Multimodality</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-4">The frontier is moving beyond text. Large Multimodal Models
                        (LMMs) can natively process and reason across text, images, audio, and even video, enabling more
                        holistic AI.</p>
                    <div class="chart-container h-80 md:h-96">
                        <canvas id="multimodalityChart"></canvas>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="kpi-card">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">The Drive for Efficiency</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-4">In response to high costs, a major trend is creating smaller,
                        faster models via techniques like quantization and knowledge distillation, enabling on-device
                        AI.</p>
                    <div class="chart-container h-80 md:h-96">
                        <canvas id="efficiencyChart"></canvas>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <footer class="text-center mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
            <p class="text-gray-600">The future of AI will be defined by a careful balance between pushing capabilities
